#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:2
msgid "Windows Hypervisor Platform"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:4
msgid ""
"Windows Hypervisor Platform is the Windows API for use of third-party "
"virtual machine monitors with hardware acceleration on Hyper-V."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:8
msgid ""
"It's implemented on top of ``Vid``, which is itself implemented on the same "
"set of hypercalls as the ``mshv`` driver on Linux."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:11
msgid ""
"WHPX is the name of the Windows Hypervisor Platform accelerator backend in "
"QEMU. It enables using QEMU with hardware acceleration on both x86_64 and "
"arm64 Windows machines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:16
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:18
msgid "WHPX requires the Windows Hypervisor Platform feature to be installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:21
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:22
msgid ""
"On client editions of Windows, that means installation through Windows "
"Features (``optionalfeatures.exe``). On server editions, feature-based "
"installation in Server Manager can be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:26
msgid ""
"Alternatively, command line installation is also possible through: ``DISM /"
"online /Enable-Feature /FeatureName:HypervisorPlatform /All``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:30
msgid "Minimum OS version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:32
msgid ""
"On x86_64, QEMU's Windows Hypervisor Platform backend is tested starting "
"from Windows 10 version 2004. Earlier Windows 10 releases *might* work but "
"are not tested."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:36
msgid ""
"On arm64, Windows 11 24H2 with the April 2025 optional updates or May 2025 "
"security updates is the minimum required release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:39
msgid ""
"Prior releases of Windows 11 version 24H2 on ARM64 shipped with a pre-"
"release version of the Windows Hypervisor Platform API, which is not "
"supported in QEMU."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:44
msgid "Quick Start"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:46
msgid "Launching a virtual machine on x86_64 with WHPX acceleration::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:48
msgid ""
"$ qemu-system-x86_64.exe -accel whpx -M pc \\\n"
"    -smp cores=2 -m 2G -device ich9-usb-ehci1 \\\n"
"    -device usb-tablet -hda OS.qcow2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:52
msgid "Launching a virtual machine on arm64 with WHPX acceleration::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:54
msgid ""
"$ qemu-system-aarch64.exe -accel whpx -M virt \\\n"
"    -cpu host -smp cores=2 -m 2G \\\n"
"    -bios edk2-aarch64-code.fd \\\n"
"    -device ramfb -device nec-usb-xhci \\\n"
"    -device usb-kbd -device usb-tablet \\\n"
"    -hda OS.qcow2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:61
msgid ""
"On arm64, for non-Windows guests, ``-device virtio-gpu-pci`` provides "
"additional functionality compared to ``-device ramfb``, but is incompatible "
"with Windows's UEFI GOP implementation, which expects a linear framebuffer "
"to be available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:67
msgid "Accelerator options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:70
msgid "x86_64"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:72
msgid ""
"``-trace whpx_unsupported_msr_access`` can be used to log accesses to "
"undocumented MSRs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:75
msgid "``-d invalid_mem`` allows to trace accesses to unmapped GPAs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:78
msgid ""
"``-accel whpx,ssd=off`` disables the separate security domain feature, as in "
"a BTB flush when entering/exiting the guest. This results in a significant "
"MMIO performance increase at the detriment of security mitigations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:84
msgid "Known issues on x86_64"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:87
msgid "Guests using legacy VGA modes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:89
msgid ""
"In guests using VGA modes that QEMU doesn't pass through framebuffer memory "
"for, performance will be quite suboptimal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:92
msgid ""
"Workaround: for affected guests, use a more modern graphics mode. "
"Alternatively, use TCG to run those guests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:96
msgid "Guests using MMX, SSE or AVX instructions for MMIO"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:98
msgid ""
"Currently, ``target/i386/emulate`` does not support guests that use MMX, SSE "
"or AVX instructions for access to MMIO memory ranges."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:101
msgid ""
"Attempts to run such guests will result in an ``Unimplemented handler`` "
"warning for MMX and a failure to decode for newer instructions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:105
msgid "PIC interrupts on Windows 10"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:107
msgid ""
"On Windows 10, a legacy PIC interrupt injected does not wake the guest from "
"an HLT when using the Hyper-V provided interrupt controller."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:110
msgid ""
"As such, on Windows 10, using the Hyper-V interrupt controller is disabled "
"by default. You can enable it via ``-M q35,pic=off`` which disables the PIC. "
"In that configuration, using a UEFI is recommended."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/whpx.rst:114
msgid ""
"On this release, ``-M kernel-irqchip=`` is not expected to be manually set "
"during normal operation. It remains as a debugging option."
msgstr ""

